<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1899-09-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1899-09-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="473" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d473">
                        <head><hi rend="italic"><persName type="from">Baron Fava</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Hill</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Translation.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Lenox,
                                        Mass.</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1899-09-23"><hi rend="italic">September 23,
                                    1899</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Thanks for your kind telegram of 21st instant. As soon as you know when
                            grand jury shall meet please wire me. You will also greatly oblige me by
                            forwarding me, if possible, copy of report of governor Louisiana with
                            its inclosures.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Fava.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>